  "base_commit": "9fe087c714d657f9baf870c231409ff984ab61e4",
  "pr_number": 1687,
  "issue_number": 1684,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Layer system applies +N/+N **counters** after the P/T **switch**, inverting CR 613.4c/613.4d sublayer order",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nIn `crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs`, layer-7 continuous-effect evaluation applies power/toughness **counters** *after* the power/toughness **switch** effect, which is the reverse of the order the Comprehensive Rules require.\n\nThe layer loop explicitly skips `Layer::CounterPT` and applies counter P/T deltas in a separate pass that runs **after** the loop completes:\n\n```rust\n// crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs:1114  (full evaluation)\nfor (layer, layer_bucket) in &effects_by_layer {\n    if matches!(*layer, Layer::Copy | Layer::CounterPT) {\n        // Copy handled above; Counter-based P/T handled separately below.\n        continue;\n    }\n    ...\n    for effect in &ordered {\n        apply_continuous_effect(state, effect);   // <- SwitchPT (Layer 7d) applied HERE, in the loop\n    }\n}\n...\n// crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs:1190\n// CR 613.4c: Power/toughness counters modify P/T in layer 7c.\nfor &id in &bf_ids {                              // <- counters applied HERE, AFTER the loop\n    ... obj.power += power_delta; obj.toughness += toughness_delta; ...\n}\n```\n\nThe P/T **switch** is `ContinuousModification::SwitchPowerToughness`, applied inside the loop:\n\n```rust\n// crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs:3406\n// CR 613.4d: Switch power and toughness values.\nContinuousModification::SwitchPowerToughness => {\n    let (p, t) = (obj.power, obj.toughness);\n    obj.power = t;\n    obj.toughness = p;\n}\n```\n\nSo the effective order is **switch (7d) \u2192 counters**, but the CR places counters in **layer 7c**, which is applied **before** the 7d switch.\n\nThe root cause is the layer enum, which invents a non-existent \"Layer 7e\" for counters and orders it *after* `SwitchPT`:\n\n```rust\n// crates/engine/src/types/layers.rs:28-33\n/// CR 613.4c: Layer 7c \u2014 Effects that modify P/T (+N/+N).\nModifyPT,\n/// CR 613.4d: Layer 7d \u2014 Effects that switch P/T.\nSwitchPT,\n/// CR 613.4c: Layer 7e \u2014 +1/+1 and -1/-1 counters modifying P/T (applied after other 7c effects).\nCounterPT,\n```\n\nThe comment cites `CR 613.4c` for `CounterPT` (correct), but then calls it \"Layer 7e\" and physically orders the variant after `SwitchPT` (7d) \u2014 there is no layer 7e in the CR, and counters are part of 7c, not a post-7d step.\n\n## What the CR actually says\n\nVerified verbatim against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`:\n\n```\n613.4c Layer 7c: Effects and counters that modify power and/or toughness\n       (but don\u2019t set power and/or toughness to a specific number or value) are applied.\n613.4d Layer 7d: Effects that switch a creature\u2019s power and toughness are applied.\n       Such effects take the value of power and apply it to the creature\u2019s toughness,\n       and take the value of toughness and apply it to the creature\u2019s power.\n```\n\n- Counters that modify P/T live in **7c** (CR 613.4c), alongside `+N/+N` effects.\n- The **switch** is **7d** (CR 613.4d), applied **after** all of 7c.\n- There is **no** \"layer 7e\" (grep for `613.4e` / `Layer 7e` in the CR returns nothing).\n\nTherefore counters must be applied **before** the switch, not after it.\n\n## Failure mode (concrete example)\n\nThe divergence is only observable with an **asymmetric** P/T counter \u2014 symmetric `+1/+1` / `-1/-1` counters commute with the swap, which is why this slips through everyday play. Asymmetric P/T counters are a first-class, parameterized type in the engine (`CounterType::PowerToughness { power, toughness }`, `crates/engine/src/types/counter.rs:16`), produced by the Oracle parser (`try_parse_counter_type` \u2192 `parse_power_toughness_counter`, `counter.rs:204`), and exercised by the engine's own test `parameterized_power_toughness_counters_apply_in_layer_7c` (`game/layers.rs:3858`, using `{0,-1}`, `{0,-2}`, `{-1,0}`).\n\nTake a 2/2 creature with one `+0/+1` counter (`PowerToughness { power: 0, toughness: 1 }`) and a continuous effect that switches its power and toughness (e.g. a *Twisted Image* / *Crookclaw Transmuter*-style \"switch this creature's power and toughness\"):\n\n- **Correct (CR 7c \u2192 7d):** counter first \u2192 `2/3`, then switch \u2192 **`3/2`**.\n- **Current engine (switch \u2192 counter):** switch first (2/2 swaps to 2/2), then counter \u2192 **`2/3`**.\n\nThe engine reports **2/3**; the rules require **3/2**. The power and toughness are transposed.\n\n(With an asymmetric *base* P/T the bug is just as reachable: a 1/1 with a `+0/+1` counter and a switch \u2192 correct `2/1`, engine `1/2`.)\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Put a creature on the battlefield (e.g. base 2/2).\n2. Give it an asymmetric P/T counter, e.g. `CounterType::PowerToughness { power: 0, toughness: 1 }`.\n3. Apply a continuous effect with `ContinuousModification::SwitchPowerToughness`.\n4. Run `evaluate_layers` and read `obj.power` / `obj.toughness`.\n5. Observe `2/3` (switch applied before the counter) instead of the rules-correct `3/2`.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nP/T counters are applied in **layer 7c (CR 613.4c)**, *before* the **layer 7d (CR 613.4d)** power/toughness switch \u2014 so the switch transposes the post-counter values.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nP/T counters are applied in a dedicated pass *after* the layer loop, i.e. after the 7d switch has already run, so the switch transposes the *pre-counter* values and the counter deltas are added to the wrong axis.\n\n## Affected code paths\n\nBoth evaluation paths share the inverted ordering:\n\n- **Full evaluation:** loop skip at `game/layers.rs:1115`; counter pass at `game/layers.rs:1190`.\n- **Incremental (entered-objects) evaluation:** loop skip at `game/layers.rs:1679`; counter pass at `game/layers.rs:1721`.\n- **Enum ordering / mislabel:** `types/layers.rs:32-33` (`CounterPT` placed after `SwitchPT`, mislabeled \"Layer 7e\").\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n- Treat counters as part of layer 7c: apply the counter P/T fold **inside** the layer loop at the `CounterPT` (7c) step positioned **before** `SwitchPT` (7d), so the existing `SwitchPT` handler observes post-counter values. Reorder the enum so `CounterPT` sits with/just after `ModifyPT` and before `SwitchPT`, and stop deferring it to a post-loop pass.\n- Within 7c, effects and counters are ordered together by timestamp/dependency per CR 613.4 \u2014 since 7c P/T modifications are purely additive they commute, so the only ordering that is observable is 7c-as-a-whole **before** 7d.\n- Correct the `types/layers.rs:32` doc comment: counters are **CR 613.4c / layer 7c**, not \"layer 7e\".\n- Add fail-on-revert coverage: a creature with an asymmetric P/T counter (e.g. `+0/+1`) plus a `SwitchPowerToughness` effect must yield the transposed *post-counter* P/T (`3/2` for a base 2/2), not the engine's current `2/3`. The existing `parameterized_power_toughness_counters_apply_in_layer_7c` test does not cover the switch interaction, and the `layer_ordering_is_correct` test only asserts the enum's own declared order, so it currently ratifies the inverted ordering rather than catching it.",
